The article discusses amendments made to Executive Order 13199 and the establishment of the President's Advisory Council for Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. The purpose of these amendments is to strengthen the ability of faith-based and other neighborhood organizations to deliver services effectively in partnership with various levels of government and private organizations. The Federal Government aims to empower these organizations while preserving constitutional commitments such as equal protection of the laws and the free exercise of religion. The article also outlines the mission, membership, and administration of the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. The Council is responsible for identifying best practices, evaluating public policies, and making recommendations for changes in policies, programs, and practices related to the delivery of services by these organizations. The article concludes with general provisions and clarifies that the order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.